-- Russia's Lenta keeps forecast for full-year sales growth at 34-38 pct
-- 
-- Thu Sep 04, 2014 02:16AM EDT
-- None



MOSCOW, Sept 4 (Reuters) - Russian food retailer Lenta <LNTAq.L> said on Thursday it was maintaining its full-year sales growth forecast of 34-38 percent despite a ban on some Western food imports.

"Lenta notes the recent trade restrictions in Russia for selected product categories and is in the process of readjusting its product offering in compliance with the new regulations," it said in a statement.